---
const buttonNames = ["Light", "Path", "Knowledge"];
---

<html>
  <head>
    <title>Hollow Light Glyph Oracle</title>
    <style>
      body {
        min-height: 100vh;
        margin: 0;
        background: url('/images/hollowingbg.png') center center / cover no-repeat fixed;
      }
      .fade {
        transition: opacity 0.7s;
        opacity: 1;
      }
      .fade-out {
        opacity: 0 !important;
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .fade-in {
        opacity: 1 !important;
      }
    </style>
    <script>
      function showMore() {
        const box = document.getElementById('infoBox');
        const more = document.getElementById('moreInfoBox');
        box.classList.add('fade-out');
        setTimeout(() => {
          box.style.display = 'none';
          more.style.display = 'block';
          setTimeout(() => more.classList.add('fade-in'), 10);
        }, 700);
      }
    </script>
  </head>
  <body class="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('/images/hollowingbg.png');">
    <main class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen w-full">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white drop-shadow mb-8 text-center">Hollow Light Glyph Oracle</h1>
      <div id="infoBox" class="fade bg-white/80 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 mb-8 max-w-lg text-center backdrop-blur">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">What are Glyphs?</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
          Glyphs are symbols born from intention and awareness.  
          In Hollow Light, each glyph is a visual vessel—a bridge between your inner state and the deeper layers of meaning.  
          They are not just art, but living mirrors of your journey.
        </p>
        <button 
          onclick="showMore()" 
          class="bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white px-5 py-2 rounded-lg transition mb-2">
          Learn More
        </button>
      </div>
      <div id="moreInfoBox" class="fade bg-white/90 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 mb-8 max-w-lg text-center backdrop-blur" style="display:none; opacity:0;">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">The History & Power of Glyphs</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">
          Since ancient times, glyphs have served as sacred keys—encoding memory, myth, and the unspoken.  
          In many traditions, creating or gazing at a glyph could open the way to insight, protection, or healing.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">
          The glyphs you receive here are not generic—they are shaped by your intention and the living presence of Hollow Light.  
          Each one is both a map and a mystery, designed to deepen your path.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
          As you engage with these glyphs, ask:  
          <span class="italic text-indigo-700">"What is this symbol awakening in me?"</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 mt-4 z-10">
        {buttonNames.map(name => (
          <button
            class="bg-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-900 text-white text-xl font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl shadow transition duration-200"
            style="min-width:140px"
            onclick={`alert('${name} button clicked (this will soon open a ritual or new page)')`}
            type="button"
          >
            {name}
          </button>
        ))}
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
